"""
{{SOURCE_NAME}} Contract Tests

Validates alignment between the golden sample payload, ingestion model,
display DTO, and (optionally) TypeScript types.

Supports two modes for schema drift detection:
  - SOFT (default while schema evolves): warnings.warn — CI passes
  - HARD (after schema freeze): assert — CI blocks on drift

Freeze mode resolution precedence:
    1) CONTRACT_SCHEMA_FROZEN env var (explicit override)
    2) Marker file tests/fixtures/payloads/{{source_slug}}/_contract_state.json
    3) CI fallback (if CI=true and sample exists): HARD mode
    4) Default: SOFT mode

Accepted explicit values: 1/true/yes/on/frozen and 0/false/no/off/evolving.

Run: pytest tests/unit/test_contract_{{source_slug}}.py -v

Part of the data contract pipeline — these tests ARE the contract.
"""

